  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In patients suffering from hypercapnic respiratory failure and treated by non invasive
      ventilation (NIV), the interest of using transcutaneous CO2 measurement to evaluate PaCO2 and
      PaCO2 variation over time is unknown and will be evaluated in this study. Measurements will
      be done during one-hour NIV treatments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
